contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionarypar|Kyle|kyle}} '''Kyle''' may refer to: * a Scottish term for a [[strait]] * [[Kyle (given name)]], a Scottish masculine given name (sometimes also given to females) * [[Kyle (surname)]], a surname of Scottish origin * [[KYLE-TV]], a Fox network affiliate ==Places== ===Canada=== * [[Kyle, Saskatchewan]], Canada ===Scotland=== * [[Kyle, Ayrshire]], Scotland (which stretched across parts of modern day [[East Ayrshire]] and [[South Ayrshire]]) * [[Kyle of Lochalsh]], [[Ross and Cromarty]] (Lieutenancy area), [[Highland (council area)]], Scotland ** [[Kyle of Lochalsh Line]], a primarily single track railway line * [[Kyle of Sutherland]], a river [[estuary]] ===United States=== * [[Kyle, Indiana]], United States * [[Kyle, South Dakota]], United States * [[Kyle, Texas]], United States ==See also== * [[Kile (disambiguation)]] * [[Kyll]] * [[Tropical Storm Kyle (disambiguation)]] {{Disambiguation|callsign}}
